    "title" : "How to make a Tooltip using TooltipDrawable in java?",
    "body" : "<p>Up to now, there is no straightforward and official way for creating a <a href=\"https://github.com/material-components/material-components-android/blob/master/docs/components/Tooltip.md\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Material Tooltip</a> in java. I know that one can create a <a href=\"https://github.com/material-components/material-components-android/blob/master/lib/java/com/google/android/material/tooltip/TooltipDrawable.java\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">TooltipDrawable</a> using:</p>\n<pre><code>TooltipDrawable tooltipDrawable = TooltipDrawable.createFromAttributes(getContext(), null, 0, labelStyle);\n</code></pre>\n<p>But attaching it to a view is a little complicated and cumbersome.</p>\n<p>I tried to extract some related part from <a href=\"https://github.com/material-components/material-components-android/blob/master/lib/java/com/google/android/material/slider/BaseSlider.java\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Material Slider source code</a> as a utility class for this reason (that I believe this is the correct way), but I couldn't do that successfully.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/gYYMw6BI.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/gYYMw6BI.png\" alt=\"Material slider with its Label\" /></a></p>\n<p>Is there a simple way to do this?</p>\n<p>P.s. I am aware of similar GitHub Repositories like <a href=\"https://github.com/skydoves/Balloon\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Balloon</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/nhaarman/supertooltips\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">superTooltips</a>.</p>\n",
